<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747185>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 19. (a,b) Nudonychocella nuda Voigt and Ernst; holotype, SMF 25383; Curfs Quarry, near Berg, Limburg, Netherlands; (a) encrusting colony, growing from top right to lower left, showing autozooids and avicularia; (b) early astogeny with the ancestrula (lower left), two budded autozooids and an avicularium (upper right). (c–f) Nudonychocella subsimplex (d’Orbigny). (c,d) NHMUK BZ 8218; Campanian,Aubeterre Formation,Plage des Nonnes,Meschers,Charente Maritime,France;(c) ancestrula and three budded autozooids, the distal autozooid with a completely preserved cryptocyst; (d) autozooids and avicularia (arrowed); (e,f) NHMUK BZ 8219; Campanian, Biron Formation, Aubeterre-sur- Dronne, Charente, France; (e) ovicellate autozooid with cap-like ovicell arrowed; (f) avicularium surrounded by autozooids. Scale bars: a = 1 mm; b, c, f = 200 µm; d = 500 µm; e = 100 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747185/files/figure.png" .

